[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rochdale 3-0 Blackpool

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Rochdale boosted their League One play-off hopes with a comfortable victory over relegation-threatened Blackpool.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Dale took the lead against the run of play just before half-time when Ashley Eastham headed in from Donal McDermott's cross.
Joe Bunney turned in Rochdale's second from close range after the visitors had failed to clear a corner.
And Nathaniel Mendez-Laing slotted home to seal the win and extend Dale's unbeaten run to three games.
The result leaves Keith Hill's side eighth in the table, four points outside the play-off places, while Blackpool are two points adrift of safety in 21st.
